==English==

===Etymology===
From the concept of [[martyrdom]] through [[fire]].

===Alternative spellings===
* '''baptism of fire'''

===Noun===
'''[[baptism]] [[by]] [[fire]]''' (''plural:'' '''[[baptisms by fire]]''')
#{{idiom}} A [[rite of passage]] through the [[survival]] or [[sucess]] of a [[crisis]].
#:''The new folks really get put through a '''baptism by fire''', to start doing a stressful job with so little training.''
#{{idiom}} A trying [[ordeal]] that was not [[experience]]d before.
#{{idiom}} A change in [[initial]] [[attitude]] or [[ideal]]s through a [[traumatic]] situation.

